## Overview
Create the integration test file skeleton with the core gating helper function.

## Deliverables

### File: `test/query_integration_test.gleam`

```gleam
// In test/query_integration_test.gleam
import support/env_helpers.{get_env}
import gleam/io
import gleeunit/should

/// Helper: Check if integration tests are enabled and log skip if not.
/// Returns True if tests should run, False if skipped.
fn integration_enabled(test_name: String) -> Bool {
  case get_env("CLAUDE_INTEGRATION_TEST") {
    Ok("1") -> True
    _ -> {
      io.println("[SKIP] " <> test_name <> " (set CLAUDE_INTEGRATION_TEST=1 to run)")
      False
    }
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] File exists at `test/query_integration_test.gleam`
- [ ] `integration_enabled()` returns `True` when `CLAUDE_INTEGRATION_TEST=1`
- [ ] `integration_enabled()` returns `False` and prints skip message otherwise
- [ ] Skip message format: `[SKIP] test_name (set CLAUDE_INTEGRATION_TEST=1 to run)`
- [ ] File compiles with `gleam build`

## Test Contract
- Tests SKIP by default (no env var set)
- All integration tests use `integration__` prefix for easy grep

## Overview
Implement preflight checks that validate the environment before running integration tests.

## Deliverables

### Helper: `is_authenticated() -> Bool`

```gleam
fn is_authenticated() -> Bool {
  // Check 1: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in environment (preferred - no subprocess)
  case get_env("ANTHROPIC_API_KEY") {
    Ok(_) -> True
    _ ->
      // Check 2: `claude auth status` with 5s timeout (if CLI supports it)
      case run_with_timeout("claude", ["auth", "status"], 5000) {
        Ok(output) if string.contains(output, "authenticated") -> True
        _ -> False  // Timeout, unsupported command, or not authenticated
      }
  }
}
```

### Test: `integration__preflight_check_test`

```gleam
pub fn integration__preflight_check_test() {
  case integration_enabled("integration__preflight_check_test") {
    True -> {
      // 1. CLI exists and version is parseable
      case find_executable("claude") {
        Error(_) -> {
          io.println("[SKIP:ENV] claude not in PATH - install CLI first")
          should.be_true(True)  // Skip, don't fail
        }
        Ok(path) -> {
          // 2. Version check (with 5s timeout)
          case detect_cli_version_with_timeout(path, 5000) {
            Error(_) -> {
              io.println("[SKIP:ENV] claude --version timed out or failed")
              should.be_true(True)
            }
            Ok(UnknownVersion(_)) -> {
              io.println("[WARN] Unparseable version - tests may fail")
            }
            Ok(CliVersion(maj, _, _, _)) if maj < 1 -> {
              io.println("[SKIP:ENV] CLI version < 1.0.0 - upgrade required")
              should.be_true(True)
            }
            Ok(_) -> {
              // 3. Required flags exist (non-network check)
              // Run: claude --help and verify flags present
              io.println("[PREFLIGHT] All checks passed - integration tests will run")
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
    False -> should.be_true(True)
  }
}
```

## Timeout Protection
- Preflight version check: 5s
- Preflight help check: 5s
- No preflight can hang indefinitely

## Skip Hierarchy
Tests skip unless ALL conditions met:
1. `CLAUDE_INTEGRATION_TEST=1` env var set
2. `claude` found in PATH (non-network check)
3. `claude --version` succeeds with 5s timeout

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `is_authenticated()` checks `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` first (no subprocess)
- [ ] `is_authenticated()` falls back to `claude auth status` with 5s timeout
- [ ] `integration__preflight_check_test` validates CLI in PATH
- [ ] `integration__preflight_check_test` validates version parseable
- [ ] Skip messages are actionable: `[SKIP:ENV] reason`
- [ ] All timeouts bounded to 5s

